    <h1>Project Title: Web-Based Water Pollution Tracking System</h1>
    <h2>Project Description</h2>
    <p>The project proposes a Web-Based Water Pollution Tracking System that enables users (citizens, authorities, NGOs) to report, visualize, and monitor pollution incidents in real-time.</p>
    <p>It aims to enhance transparency, accountability, and community engagement in environmental protection efforts.</p>

    <p>HTML entities: &AMP; &copy; &lt; &gt;</p>
    <div>
        <img src="images/wastewater.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="142">
    </div>
    <div>
        <p>Project Features:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Real-time reporting of pollution incidents</li>
            <li>Interactive map for visualizing pollution hotspots</li>
            <li>User-friendly interface for easy navigation</li>
            <li>Data analytics for trend analysis and reporting</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Technologies Used:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>HTML, CSS, JavaScript for front-end development</li>
            <li>Node.js and Express for back-end services</li>
            <li>MongoDB for database management</li>
            <li>Google Maps API for location services</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Project Goals:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Increase public awareness of water pollution issues</li>
            <li>Facilitate community involvement in environmental protection</li>
            <li>Provide a platform for data-driven decision making</li>
            <li>Enhance collaboration between citizens and authorities</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
